  "response": "The promise made by the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) regarding depositing 15 lakhs into every Indian's bank account was a significant political statement made during the 2014 general elections. However, such promises are often complex and depend on various factors, including economic viability, policy implementation, and political circumstances. \n\nAs of my last knowledge update in October 2023, this promise had not been realized, and it remains a topic of debate and discussion among political analysts and the public. Many view such promises within the context of electoral rhetoric rather than actionable policies. For a definitive answer on whether it will ever come true, it would require insight into future political developments, government priorities, and economic conditions in India.",
